<p id="Par27" class="p">A distinction can be made whether or not S has to operate under an external global abatement constraint. Suppose that all countries agreed that a required level of global abatement (
 <italic class="italic">A</italic>
 <sup class="sup">∘</sup>), e.g., stipulated by the IPCC relative to BAU emissions, has to be met. This will add a pollution constraint to the exercise, and the only decision by S is to assign the abatement burdens 
 <italic class="italic">A</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">i</italic>
 </sub> such that their sum equal 
 <italic class="italic">A</italic>
 <sup class="sup">∘</sup>. Thus, S maximizes welfare over all countries subject to the global abatement constraint and all national resource constraints:
